      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.executeWorkflowTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.1,
      "position": [
        0,
        0
      ],
      "id": "c1000001-0001-4001-8001-000000000001",
      "name": "Trigger"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "={{ $('Trigger').item.json.text }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are the Dojo AI Supervisor for a martial arts dojo management system. Analyze the user request and route it to the correct specialist agent(s).\n\n## Specialist Agents\n\n- **AttendanceAgent** — check-ins, check-outs, class schedules, attendance history\n- **EnrollmentAgent** — session enrollment, unenrollment, course roster management, waitlist\n- **CoreAgent** — belt promotions/tests, member create/update/lookup, calendar events, tasks, programs\n- **SubscriptionsAgent** — subscriptions, billing, invoices, payments, credits, plan changes, pauses, cancellations\n- **CommunicationsAgent** — email, SMS, guardian contact, discuss channels, marketing campaigns, social posts\n- **GeneralAgent** — CRM leads, sales orders, accounting, HR, anything not covered by the above\n\n## Decision Rules\n\n1. **Single domain**: Call exactly ONE specialist with the full user request.\n2. **Multi domain**: Decompose the request into sub-tasks. Call each specialist IN SEQUENCE with only its relevant sub-task as user_request.\n3. **Result-passing**: When a later step needs data from an earlier step — e.g. member names from an invoice list — extract that data from the prior tool's response and embed it explicitly in the next user_request. NEVER send a vague task like \"get profiles for each overdue member\" without the actual names. Instead write: \"Get profiles for Jordan Smith, Sarah Lee, Mike Johnson\".\n4. **For-each batching**: For \"for each X\" requests, collect all X items from the prior step and pass them as a single list in one agent call. Do not loop one item at a time.\n5. **Pending confirmation**: If a specialist tool returns a JSON response where `state` is `pending_confirmation` — STOP immediately. Return that specialist's `response` text verbatim. Do NOT call any more specialists or tools.\n6. **Help / capability questions**: Answer directly from the specialist list above. Do not call any tools.\n7. **Step logging**: After each specialist completes, call Push_Step with: step_num (1-based integer, increment per agent called), agent_display_name (human-readable name e.g. \"Subscriptions Agent\"), agent_tool_name (exact tool name e.g. \"SubscriptionsAgent\"), result_summary (what the agent returned — include key data: names, amounts, counts, 1-3 sentences), reasoning (why you routed this sub-task to this agent and what you plan to do next).\n8. **Final reply**: After all specialists complete, compose a comprehensive natural-prose reply. For \"summarize\" or \"overview\" requests: cover each step's key findings, include totals and important data points, and add actionable insights. For simple single-domain requests: one or two concise sentences is fine.\n\n## Context\n\nUser role: {{ $('Trigger').item.json.role }}\n\nConversation history:\n{{ $('Trigger').item.json.conversation_history }}\n\nLive database context:\n{{ $('Trigger').item.json.db_context }}\n\nAdvisory domain from vector search: {{ $('Trigger').item.json.agent }}"
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        280,
        0
      ],
      "id": "c1000001-0001-4001-8001-000000000002",
      "name": "Supervisor AI Agent",
      "retryOnFail": true,
      "maxTries": 2
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "model": {
          "__rl": true,
          "value": "gpt-4o",
          "mode": "list",
          "cachedResultName": "gpt-4o"
        },
        "options": {
          "temperature": 0.2
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatOpenAi",
      "typeVersion": 1.3,
      "position": [
        80,
        220
      ],
      "id": "c1000001-0001-4001-8001-000000000003",
      "name": "OpenAI Chat Model",
      "credentials": {
        "openAiApi": {
          "id": "Jzdr2yiErsFuHEyP",
          "name": "OpenAI account"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "toolDescription": "Log a completed agent step to Odoo. Call this AFTER each specialist agent completes — not before. Provide: step_num (1-based integer, increment per agent called), agent_display_name (human-readable name e.g. 'Subscriptions Agent'), agent_tool_name (exact tool name e.g. 'SubscriptionsAgent'), result_summary (1-3 sentences of what the agent returned — include key data: names, amounts, counts), reasoning (why you routed this sub-task to this agent).",
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "http://web:8069/dojo/ai/step",
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={{ JSON.stringify({ pipeline_key: $('Trigger').item.json.pipeline_key || '', step_num: parseInt($fromAI('step_num', 'Step number, 1-based integer, increment for each agent')) || 1, name: $fromAI('agent_display_name', 'Human-readable agent name e.g. Subscriptions Agent'), agent_name: $fromAI('agent_tool_name', 'Exact tool name used e.g. SubscriptionsAgent'), detail: $fromAI('result_summary', 'What the agent returned - include key data like names amounts counts. 1-3 sentences.') + ' | Why: ' + $fromAI('reasoning', 'Why you routed this sub-task to this agent') }) }}",
        "options": {
          "timeout": 3000,
          "response": {
            "response": {
              "neverError": true
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequestTool",
      "typeVersion": 4.4,
      "position": [
        300,
        220
      ],
      "id": "c1000001-0001-4001-8001-000000000004",
      "name": "Push_Step"
    },
